    <description>Bitwy XXI Wieku (Battles of XXIth Century) is a wargame system taking place in the first decades of XXIth century. The game contains maps for central Europe, Ukraine and Iraq. The units belong to the Polish, Russian, American, Iraqi, German, Ukrainian and British armies.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The counters use NATO symbols, while each units has points table for different equipment for different conflicts - for example, the three tables for polish armored units are for T-72, PT-91 and Leopard tanks.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each hex represents one kilometer and each counter a company. The game will be also available with wooden tiles instead of counters. There are three scenarios:&amp;#10;- Russian attack in Bartoszyce area, Poland, in 2014&amp;#10;- Ukrainian-Russian fights in Crimea in 2014&amp;#10;- British attack on Basra during second Iraq war in 2003&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Following scenarios were published in the &amp;quot;Taktyka i Strategia&amp;quot; magazine:&amp;#10;- Bia&amp;#197;&amp;#130;y Konw&amp;oacute;j (2/2014)&amp;#10;- &amp;quot;Japkowa&amp;quot; Wojna (2/2014)&amp;#10;- Operacja &amp;quot;Stra&amp;#197;&amp;#188; na Eufracie&amp;quot; (2/2014)&amp;#10;- Krymskie dzieci (1/2015)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
